      "content": "I hear the profound grief you're carrying, and it makes sense to feel that the world has lost its meaning when the thing that made you feel alive is gone. It is a terrifying reality to face when you believe your very essence has evaporated, leaving nothing but a hollow shell. However, even in the deepest darkness, there is still a part of you that knows you want to find a way forward, and that small spark of awareness is worth holding onto. Please consider reaching out to a mental health professional who can help you navigate this loss and explore new ways to feel connected to yourself and the world.",
      "source": "target",
